 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P03-T064 (Research Set / filtering / structured comparison; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Sixty-fourth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S5-P03). Aligns the research-set benefit of Elicit/Consensus: collect papers into a Research Set, extract structured method/sample/result fields, and compare them side by side -- WITHOUT guessing. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a read-only library, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/research_set.py: extract_fields (label/statistic-driven method/sample/result extraction where every value is a BYTE-EXACT span of the source with an evidence locator offset+length+quote, and a field with no marker is reported {value:None, status:'missing'} -- 缺失不猜, never fabricated), make_set (a Research Set collection, deterministic order), comparison_table (per-paper rows x method/sample/result columns, each cell value+evidence or a missing flag), filter_set (reproducible has-field / keyword filtering, deterministic order), and traces_to_source (every non-missing value is byte-exact at its recorded source offset). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P03-T064/: research_set_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P03-T064/test-results/research_set_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): every one of the 10 present Golden-Set fields traces byte-for-byte back to its source span (value == text[offset:offset+length], quote == value) and matches the hand label; all 5 intentionally-absent fields are reported missing with no fabricated value; a hallucinated value and a guess-a-default extractor are BOTH rejected by the traceability check (so the 回原文 guarantee is non-vacuous); and has-field filtering is identical across 3 runs, deterministically ordered and a non-trivial subset (P001/P002/P005), while a keyword filter yields a different set (P001/P003). Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P03-T063 (research metadata enhancement: DOI/Crossref/OpenAlex; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Sixty-third task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (opens S5-P03). Enriches an arXiv paper's identity, authors, institutions, version, and citation graph with DOI/Crossref/OpenAlex metadata while ALWAYS keeping the original arXiv paper as the evidence anchor -- enhancement is additive and source-tagged, never a replacement or a block. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a read-only enhancement library, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/research_metadata.py: make_crossref_adapter / make_openalex_adapter (fixture-backed; return an enhancement, None when not found, or raise AdapterError on a transient failure), enhance (attaches additive source-tagged enhancements; the original paper is deepcopied as an immutable evidence anchor; each adapter receives a throwaway copy so it cannot corrupt the anchor; ANY adapter exception -- not just AdapterError -- is recorded as failed and never blocks), run_pipeline (degraded fallback: a failure never drops a paper), link_works (a preprint links to a journal version ONLY when Crossref's has_preprint_arxiv_id confirms THIS arXiv id; the two versions stay distinct in type and evidence -- the preprint is never relabeled, an unconfirmed DOI never links), and resolve_authors (reuses T058 entity_resolver to unify authors across Crossref+OpenAlex with provenance). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P03-T063/: research_metadata_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P03-T063/test-results/research_metadata_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): preprint vs journal not confused -- a confirmed publication yields a preprint version (arXiv evidence) and a journal version (Crossref DOI evidence) linked under one work but distinct, the preprint never relabeled; an unconfirmed DOI adds no journal version (and confirming it WOULD, proving the gate is load-bearing); two same-title papers are not merged. Enhancement failure does not block the original paper -- 5 papers in, 5 out, blocked 0 even with Crossref/OpenAlex failures, original evidence byte-identical and never mutated, failures recorded as failed not silently not_found, a KeyError-raising (non-AdapterError) adapter still keeps all papers, and a mutating adapter cannot corrupt the anchor, while a drop-on-failure pipeline would keep only 2/5. Authors unified across both sources without confusing distinct people. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
